    <note>Wang(2) Huaiyin [10042] Compiler with others of the Taiping shenghui fang, 100 ch. comissioned by imperial edict in 982. (Ding Fubao, 477 ff.; SS, YWZ, 6.28b; Gest call number 7976/1197. SKTY, 103.5b has author as Wang Huaide in error. Huaiyin was originally a taoist priest (daoshi), who lived in the Songzhou, Songcheng (modern Shangqiu) Jianlong guan (Jianlong Taoist temple). In ca. 977 he returned to lay life at the request of Zhao(1) Taizong [9001] and was appointed Shangyao fengyu. After three promotions, he became Hanlin Yiguan. In 986, he was granted a residence (zhai) in Kaifeng (SHY:FYu, 4.22b). CBD, p. 373.From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:986:  Granted, as Hanlin yiguan, a residence (zhai) in Kaifeng.</note>
